--- Section 1: Framework's three sharp claims ---
  #    Framework                                 SM                              BSM (typical)                 
  E1   θ_eff = 0 EXACTLY                         free param ≤ 10⁻¹⁰              varies; often non-zero        
  E2   d_n(QCD) = 0 EXACTLY                      ≤ 10⁻²⁶ e·cm × θ/10⁻¹⁰          typically larger if θ ≠ 0     
  E3   All theta-induced EDMs = 0 (universal)    individual untested at θ→0      distinct from BSM             

--- Section 2: d_n predicted vs n2EDM sensitivity ---
  Source                       d_n (e·cm)    Detectable by n2EDM (~1e-28)?
  Framework: CKM-only             1.00e-32    NO (4 orders below)
  SM (free θ ≤ 10⁻¹⁰)             1.00e-26    YES (potentially)
  SUSY (MSSM, generic)            1.00e-27    YES
  Multi-Higgs                     1.00e-27    YES
  Axion (Peccei-Quinn)            1.00e-32    NO

  Current bound: d_n < 1.8 × 10⁻²⁶ e·cm (PSI 2020, Abel et al)
  n2EDM target (2027+): σ(d_n) ≈ 10⁻²⁸ e·cm

--- Section 3: Three n2EDM discrimination scenarios ---
  E-1   n2EDM detects d_n at 10⁻²⁸ to 10⁻²⁶ e·cm
        Framework: STRONGLY DISFAVORED to FALSIFIED
        Interpretation: Signal too large for CKM-only; BSM CP source

  E-2   n2EDM sets bound d_n < 10⁻²⁸ with no detection
        Framework: CONSISTENT
        Interpretation: Constrains BSM; doesn't discriminate framework from SM-axion

  E-3   n2EDM (or successor) detects d_n at CKM level (~10⁻³²)
        Framework: NEUTRAL / WEAKLY SUPPORTED
        Interpretation: Beyond n2EDM precision; future-future experiments


--- Section 4: Axion null test ---
  Framework predicts NO axion mechanism needed (θ_eff = 0 structural).

  Discrimination via axion experiments:
    Axion DETECTED (ADMX, IAXO, BabyIAXO):
      → Framework's 'no axion needed' loses motivation but not strictly falsified
    Axion NOT DETECTED at projected ADMX-EFR/IAXO sensitivity:
      → Framework's 'no axion needed' claim STRENGTHENED

--- Section 5: Universal EDM vanishing — multi-species tests ---
  EDM species              Framework prediction      Experiments
  neutron d_n                0 (CKM-only ~10⁻³²)        n2EDM, future
  electron d_e               0 (CKM contribution)       ACME-III, future
  199-Hg atomic              0 (nuclear/atomic CP)      Hg EDM experiments
  muon d_μ                   0 (weak-sector CKM)        muon EDM proposals

  Multi-species correlated detection consistent with single θ-source
  would be inconsistent with framework's universal vanishing claim.

--- Section 6: Honest discrimination assessment ---
  Distinguishing power vs SM-CKM-only: LOW (both predict same ~10⁻³²)
  Distinguishing power vs SM-without-axion: MODERATE
    (framework structurally forbids what SM allows)
  Distinguishing power vs BSM with new CP sources: HIGH
    (n2EDM detection >10⁻³⁰ would falsify framework's CKM-only)

  Best near-term discrimination: n2EDM @ PSI 2027+
  - Detection at 10⁻²⁸: framework FALSIFIED (BSM source confirmed)
  - Null result at 10⁻²⁸: framework CONSISTENT, BSM constrained
  - n2EDM cannot reach the predicted CKM-only ~10⁻³²

